ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for taking the time to get in touch & leaving your thoughts on the changes we've made.  The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: YOU HAVE RECENTLY CHANGED THE JAR SHAPE,FOR THE WORSE,MORE DIFFICULT TO HOLD AND NOT AS VISUALLY ATTRACTIVE.ALSO YOUR COFFEE NOW LEAVES A RESIDUE IN THE BOOTOM OF THE CUP
Results.Title: POOR JAR SHAPE

ClientResponses.Response: We're sad to hear you're not enjoying the changes we've made but thank you for taking the time & letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: I like the ease of instant,  but still want a decent tasting coffee and this is what you get with Nescafe and this one in particular. Not bitter but tastes deep and rich.

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you for leaving your comments! Due to the addition of micro ground coffee during the recent change there may be a residue at the bottom of your cup. Micro ground coffee is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! It's sad to hear you don't agree with the changes we've made but your feedback is really important to us!
